author: @marvinbraga
text: Hello Harrison!  Congratulations and thank you for your videos! I'm learning a lot.  I would like to give a simple suggestion for solving a small problem that I encountered during encoding.  In the eleventh video, file "mysite/main/views.py", in the implementation of the "single_slug" method, I suggest the creation of the "tut" variable.  Instead of the code being so ...         for m in matching_series.all():             part_one = Tutorial.objects.filter(tutorial_series__tutorial_series=m.tutorial_series).earliest("tutorial_published")             series_urls[m] = part_one.tutorial_slug  To become like this ...         for m in matching_series.all():             tut = Tutorial.objects.filter(series__series=m.series)             if tut.count() > 0:                 part_one = tut.earliest("published")                 series_urls[m] = part_one.slug  I hope I've helped a bit! Hugs! Sincerely.

author: @meesbroer9006
text: To avoid the unintuitive double underscore when finding the matching series, you could instead find the category with TutorialCategories.objects.get(category_slug=single_slug) and then get it's series set. So you would get TutorialCategories.objects.get(category_slug=single_slug).tutorialseries_set.all().
